l-align: -1.838ex; width:67.421ex; height:4.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
sigma =3D{\sqrt {\mathrm {average} \left((v-\mu )^{2}{\text{ for }}v\in \ma=
thrm {values} \right)}}{\text{ where }}\mu =3D\mathrm {average} (\mathrm {v=
alues} ).}"></span>
</p><p>These eight data points have the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Mean" title=3D"Mean">mean</a> (average) of 5:
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle \mu =3D{\frac {2+4+4+4+5+5+7+9}{8}}=3D{\frac {40}{8}}=3D5.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>=CE=BC<!-- =CE=BC --></mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mn>2</mn>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mn>4</mn>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mn>4</mn>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mn>4</mn>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mn>5</mn>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mn>5</mn>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mn>7</mn>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mn>9</mn>
            </mrow>
            <mn>8</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>40</mn>
            <mn>8</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>5.</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \mu =3D{\frac=
 {2+4+4+4+5+5+7+9}{8}}=3D{\frac {40}{8}}=3D5.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/f566086ff19d3f2c608acdd3bdd810a8e8f8958a" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -1.838ex; width:45.686ex; height:5.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
mu =3D{\frac {2+4+4+4+5+5+7+9}{8}}=3D{\frac {40}{8}}=3D5.}"></span>
</p><p>First, calculate the deviations of each data point from the mean, an=
