<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Standard_deviation_of_avera=
ge_height_for_adult_men">Standard deviation of average height for adult men=
</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">=
[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DStandard_de=
viation&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit section: Standard =
deviation of average height for adult men"><span>edit</span></a><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>If the population of interest is approximately normally distributed, the=
 standard deviation provides information on the proportion of observations =
above or below certain values. For example, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Average_human_height" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Average =
human height">average height for adult men</a> in the <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States" title=3D"United States">United States</a=
> is about <span class=3D"rt-commentedText tooltip tooltip-dotted" title=3D=
"175&nbsp;cm; 5&nbsp;ft 9&nbsp;in">69&nbsp;inches</span>,<sup id=3D"cite_re=
f-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standard_=
deviation#cite_note-4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> with a standard deviation of around <link=
 rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r10388=
41319"><span class=3D"rt-commentedText tooltip tooltip-dotted" title=3D"7.6=
&nbsp;cm">3&nbsp;inches</span>. This means that most men (about 68%, assumi=
ng a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Normal_distribution" title=3D=
"Normal distribution">normal distribution</a>) have a height within 3&nbsp;=
inches of the mean (<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-d=
ata:TemplateStyles:r1038841319"><span class=3D"rt-commentedText tooltip too=
ltip-dotted" title=3D"168=E2=80=93183&nbsp;cm; 5&nbsp;ft 6&nbsp;in&nbsp;=E2=
=80=93 6&nbsp;ft 0&nbsp;in">66=E2=80=9372&nbsp;inches</span>)&nbsp;=E2=80=
=93 one standard deviation&nbsp;=E2=80=93 and almost all men (about 95%) ha=
ve a height within <link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-da=
ta:TemplateStyles:r1038841319"><span class=3D"rt-commentedText tooltip tool=
