lass=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The standard deviation of a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Con=
tinuous_distribution" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Continuous distributio=
n">continuous real-valued random variable</a> <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" =
style=3D"font-style:italic;">X</span> with <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Probability_density_function" title=3D"Probability density functio=
n">probability density function</a> <span class=3D"texhtml"><var style=3D"p=
adding-right: 1px;">p</var>(<var style=3D"padding-right: 1px;">x</var>)</sp=
an> is
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle \sigma =3D{\sqrt {\int _{\mathbf {X} }\left(x-\mu \right)^{2}\,=
p(x)\,{\mathrm {d} }x}}\,,~~{\text{ where }}~~\mu \equiv \int _{\mathbf {X}=
 }x\,p(x)\,{\mathrm {d} }x\,,}">
