span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CE=BC</span> is t=
he arithmetic mean), about 95 percent are within two standard deviations (<=
span class=3D"texhtml"><var style=3D"padding-right: 1px;">=CE=BC</var> =C2=
=B1 2<var style=3D"padding-right: 1px;">=CF=83</var></span>), and about 99.=
7 percent lie within three standard deviations (<span class=3D"texhtml"><va=
r style=3D"padding-right: 1px;">=CE=BC</var> =C2=B1 3<var style=3D"padding-=
