{\sqrt {{\frac {1}{N-1}}\sum _{i=3D1}^{N}\left(x_{i}-r\right)^{2}}}.}</anno=
tation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/30bc6e0d1f4590e78328e37675e663281c10c015" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -3.005ex; width:30.3ex; height:8.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \si=
gma (r)=3D{\sqrt {{\frac {1}{N-1}}\sum _{i=3D1}^{N}\left(x_{i}-r\right)^{2}=
}}.}"></span>
</p><p>Using <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calculus" title=3D"Ca=
lculus">calculus</a> or by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complet=
ing_the_square" title=3D"Completing the square">completing the square</a>, =
it is possible to show that <span class=3D"texhtml"><var style=3D"padding-r=
ight: 1px;">=CF=83</var>(<var style=3D"padding-right: 1px;">r</var>)</span>=
 has a unique minimum at the mean:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle r=3D{\bar {x}}.\,}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>r</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mover>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">=C2=AF<!-- =C2=AF --></mo>
            </mover>
          </mrow>
        </mrow>
