          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mtext>mean</mtext>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <msqrt>
              <mi>N</mi>
            </msqrt>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mi>=CF=83<!-- =CF=83 --></mi>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \sigma _{\tex=
t{mean}}=3D{\frac {1}{\sqrt {N}}}\sigma ,}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/cedd365da677eb61bf79a706391e3f6305d80394" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.838ex; width:15.305ex; height:6.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
sigma _{\text{mean}}=3D{\frac {1}{\sqrt {N}}}\sigma ,}"></span>
</p><p>where <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">N</s=
pan> is the number of observations in the sample used to estimate the mean.=
 This can easily be proven with (see <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Variance#Basic_properties" title=3D"Variance">basic properties of the va=
riance</a>):
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
