                  <mfrac>
                    <mn>1</mn>
                    <mi>N</mi>
                  </mfrac>
                </mrow>
                <mi>var</mi>
                <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
                <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
                <mi>X</mi>
                <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
                <mo>.</mo>
              </mtd>
            </mtr>
          </mtable>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\begin{align=
ed}\operatorname {var} ({\text{mean}})&amp;=3D\operatorname {var} \left({\f=
rac {1}{N}}\sum _{i=3D1}^{N}X_{i}\right)=3D{\frac {1}{N^{2}}}\operatorname =
{var} \left(\sum _{i=3D1}^{N}X_{i}\right)\\&amp;=3D{\frac {1}{N^{2}}}\sum _=
{i=3D1}^{N}\operatorname {var} (X_{i})=3D{\frac {N}{N^{2}}}\operatorname {v=
ar} (X)=3D{\frac {1}{N}}\operatorname {var} (X).\end{aligned}}}</annotation=
>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/b0419885b09d9d4523ac2ac10293c9dd8d1e69b7" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -6.838ex; width:59.074ex; height:14.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle =
{\begin{aligned}\operatorname {var} ({\text{mean}})&amp;=3D\operatorname {v=
ar} \left({\frac {1}{N}}\sum _{i=3D1}^{N}X_{i}\right)=3D{\frac {1}{N^{2}}}\=
operatorname {var} \left(\sum _{i=3D1}^{N}X_{i}\right)\\&amp;=3D{\frac {1}{=
N^{2}}}\sum _{i=3D1}^{N}\operatorname {var} (X_{i})=3D{\frac {N}{N^{2}}}\op=
eratorname {var} (X)=3D{\frac {1}{N}}\operatorname {var} (X).\end{aligned}}=
}"></span>
</p><p>Resulting in:
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle \sigma _{\text{mean}}=3D{\frac {\sigma }{\sqrt {N}}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>=CF=83<!-- =CF=83 --></mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mtext>mean</mtext>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mi>=CF=83<!-- =CF=83 --></mi>
            <msqrt>
              <mi>N</mi>
            </msqrt>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \sigma _{\tex=
t{mean}}=3D{\frac {\sigma }{\sqrt {N}}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/89df028af1a042901a16b631764dcfc3c6da6f05" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.838ex; width:13.975ex; height:5.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
sigma _{\text{mean}}=3D{\frac {\sigma }{\sqrt {N}}}.}"></span>
</p><p>In order to estimate the standard deviation of the mean <span class=
=3D"texhtml"><var style=3D"padding-right: 1px;">=CF=83</var><sub>mean</sub>=
</span> it is necessary to know the standard deviation of the entire popula=
tion <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CF=83</span=
> beforehand. However, in most applications this parameter is unknown. For =
example, if a series of 10 measurements of a previously unknown quantity is=
 performed in a laboratory, it is possible to calculate the resulting sampl=
e mean and sample standard deviation, but it is impossible to calculate the=
 standard deviation of the mean. However, one can estimate the standard dev=
iation of the entire population from the sample, and thus obtain an estimat=
e for the standard error of the mean.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Rapid_calculation_methods">=
Rapid calculation methods</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D=
"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/inde=
x.php?title=3DStandard_deviation&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D27" title=
=3D"Edit section: Rapid calculation methods"><span>edit</span></a><span cla=
ss=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
See also: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algorithms_for_calculati=
ng_variance" title=3D"Algorithms for calculating variance">Algorithms for c=
alculating variance</a></div>
<p>The following two formulas can represent a running (repeatedly updated) =
standard deviation. A set of two power sums <span class=3D"texhtml"><var st=
yle=3D"padding-right: 1px;">s</var><sub>1</sub></span> and <span class=3D"t=
exhtml"><var style=3D"padding-right: 1px;">s</var><sub>2</sub></span> are c=
omputed over a set of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:ital=
ic;">N</span> values of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:it=
alic;">x</span>, denoted as <span class=3D"texhtml"><var style=3D"padding-r=
ight: 1px;">x</var><sub>1</sub>, ..., <var style=3D"padding-right: 1px;">x<=
/var><sub><var style=3D"padding-right: 1px;">N</var></sub></span>:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle s_{j}=3D\sum _{k=3D1}^{N}{x_{k}^{j}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>s</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>j</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <munderover>
          <mo>=E2=88=91<!-- =E2=88=91 --></mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>k</mi>
            <mo>=3D</mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>N</mi>
          </mrow>
        </munderover>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <msubsup>
            <mi>x</mi>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mi>k</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mi>j</mi>
            </mrow>
          </msubsup>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle s_{j}=3D\sum =
_{k=3D1}^{N}{x_{k}^{j}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/ee1c89853814962100a032c587649cfd8947786b" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -3.005ex; width:11.906ex; height:7.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle s=
_{j}=3D\sum _{k=3D1}^{N}{x_{k}^{j}}.}"></span>
</p><p>Given the results of these running summations, the values <span clas=
s=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">N</span>, <span class=3D"te=
xhtml"><var style=3D"padding-right: 1px;">s</var><sub>1</sub></span>, <span=
 class=3D"texhtml"><var style=3D"padding-right: 1px;">s</var><sub>2</sub></=
span> can be used at any time to compute the <i>current</i> value of the ru=
nning standard deviation:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle \sigma =3D{\frac {\sqrt {Ns_{2}-s_{1}^{2}}}{N}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>=CF=83<!-- =CF=83 --></mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <msqrt>
              <mi>N</mi>
              <msub>
                <mi>s</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <msubsup>
                <mi>s</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>1</mn>
                </mrow>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msubsup>
            </msqrt>
            <mi>N</mi>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \sigma =3D{\f=
rac {\sqrt {Ns_{2}-s_{1}^{2}}}{N}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/d018f4cc3c133c25e9477b1f0cf23d8c35e8a44a" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -1.838ex; width:17.428ex; height:7.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
sigma =3D{\frac {\sqrt {Ns_{2}-s_{1}^{2}}}{N}}.}"></span>
</p><p>Where <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">N</s=
pan>, as mentioned above, is the size of the set of values (or can also be =
regarded as <span class=3D"texhtml"><var style=3D"padding-right: 1px;">s</v=
ar><sub>0</sub></span>).
</p><p>Similarly for sample standard deviation,
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle s=3D{\sqrt {\frac {Ns_{2}-s_{1}^{2}}{N(N-1)}}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>s</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <msqrt>
            <mfrac>
              <mrow>
                <mi>N</mi>
                <msub>
                  <mi>s</mi>
                  <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <mn>2</mn>
                  </mrow>
                </msub>
                <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                <msubsup>
                  <mi>s</mi>
                  <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <mn>1</mn>
                  </mrow>
                  <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <mn>2</mn>
                  </mrow>
                </msubsup>
              </mrow>
              <mrow>
                <mi>N</mi>
                <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
                <mi>N</mi>
                <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                <mn>1</mn>
                <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
              </mrow>
            </mfrac>
          </msqrt>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle s=3D{\sqrt {\=
frac {Ns_{2}-s_{1}^{2}}{N(N-1)}}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/6f0383a0ab52653ebcf7a2379df4d3fb588669a6" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -3.005ex; width:17.935ex; height:7.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle s=
=3D{\sqrt {\frac {Ns_{2}-s_{1}^{2}}{N(N-1)}}}.}"></span>
</p><p>In a computer implementation, as the two <span class=3D"texhtml"><va=
r style=3D"padding-right: 1px;">s</var><sub><var style=3D"padding-right: 1p=
x;">j</var></sub></span> sums become large, we need to consider <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Round-off_error" title=3D"Round-off error">ro=
und-off error</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arithmetic_over=
flow" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Arithmetic overflow">arithmetic overfl=
ow</a>, and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arithmetic_underflow" =
title=3D"Arithmetic underflow">arithmetic underflow</a>. The method below c=
alculates the running sums method with reduced rounding errors.<sup id=3D"c=
ite_ref-17" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/St=
andard_deviation#cite_note-17"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> This is a "one pass" algorithm f=
or calculating variance of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style=
:italic;">n</span> samples without the need to store prior data during the =
calculation. Applying this method to a time series will result in successiv=
e values of standard deviation corresponding to <span class=3D"texhtml mvar=
" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span> data points as <span class=3D"texht=
ml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span> grows larger with each new s=
ample, rather than a constant-width sliding window calculation.
</p><p>For <span class=3D"texhtml"><var style=3D"padding-right: 1px;">k</va=
r> =3D 1, ..., <var style=3D"padding-right: 1px;">n</var></span>:
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle {\begin{aligned}A_{0}&amp;=3D0\\A_{k}&amp;=3DA_{k-1}+{\=
frac {x_{k}-A_{k-1}}{k}}\end{aligned}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mtable columnalign=3D"right left right left right left right lef=
t right left right left" rowspacing=3D"3pt" columnspacing=3D"0em 2em 0em 2e=
m 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em" displaystyle=3D"true">
            <mtr>
              <mtd>
                <msub>
                  <mi>A</mi>
                  <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <mn>0</mn>
                  </mrow>
                </msub>
              </mtd>
              <mtd>
                <mi></mi>
                <mo>=3D</mo>
                <mn>0</mn>
              </mtd>
            </mtr>
            <mtr>
              <mtd>
                <msub>
                  <mi>A</mi>
                  <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <mi>k</mi>
                  </mrow>
                </msub>
              </mtd>
              <mtd>
                <mi></mi>
                <mo>=3D</mo>
                <msub>
                  <mi>A</mi>
                  <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <mi>k</mi>
                    <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                    <mn>1</mn>
                  </mrow>
                </msub>
                <mo>+</mo>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mfrac>
                    <mrow>
                      <msub>
                        <mi>x</mi>
                        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                          <mi>k</mi>
                        </mrow>
                      </msub>
                      <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                      <msub>
                        <mi>A</mi>
                        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                          <mi>k</mi>
                          <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                          <mn>1</mn>
                        </mrow>
                      </msub>
                    </mrow>
                    <mi>k</mi>
                  </mfrac>
                </mrow>
              </mtd>
            </mtr>
          </mtable>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\begin{align=
ed}A_{0}&amp;=3D0\\A_{k}&amp;=3DA_{k-1}+{\frac {x_{k}-A_{k-1}}{k}}\end{alig=
ned}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/0855aebe6c22c37d63d2f1b9b830a1ecccd5bcb6" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -3.671ex; width:25.482ex; height:8.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {=
\begin{aligned}A_{0}&amp;=3D0\\A_{k}&amp;=3DA_{k-1}+{\frac {x_{k}-A_{k-1}}{=
k}}\end{aligned}}}"></span>
</p><p>where <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">A</s=
pan> is the mean value.
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle {\begin{aligned}Q_{0}&amp;=3D0\\Q_{k}&amp;=3DQ_{k-1}+{\frac {k-=
1}{k}}\left(x_{k}-A_{k-1}\right)^{2}\\&amp;=3DQ_{k-1}+\left(x_{k}-A_{k-1}\r=
ight)\left(x_{k}-A_{k}\right)\end{aligned}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mtable columnalign=3D"right left right left right left right lef=
t right left right left" rowspacing=3D"3pt" columnspacing=3D"0em 2em 0em 2e=
m 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em" displaystyle=3D"true">
            <mtr>
              <mtd>
                <msub>
                  <mi>Q</mi>
                  <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <mn>0</mn>
                  </mrow>
                </msub>
              </mtd>
              <mtd>
                <mi></mi>
                <mo>=3D</mo>
                <mn>0</mn>
              </mtd>
            </mtr>
            <mtr>
              <mtd>
                <msub>
                  <mi>Q</mi>
                  <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <mi>k</mi>
                  </mrow>
                </msub>
              </mtd>
              <mtd>
                <mi></mi>
                <mo>=3D</mo>
                <msub>
                  <mi>Q</mi>
                  <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <mi>k</mi>
                    <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                    <mn>1</mn>
                  </mrow>
                </msub>
                <mo>+</mo>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mfrac>
                    <mrow>
                      <mi>k</mi>
                      <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                      <mn>1</mn>
                    </mrow>
                    <mi>k</mi>
                  </mfrac>
                </mrow>
                <msup>
                  <mrow>
                    <mo>(</mo>
                    <mrow>
                      <msub>
                        <mi>x</mi>
                        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                          <mi>k</mi>
                        </mrow>
                      </msub>
                      <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                      <msub>
                        <mi>A</mi>
                        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                          <mi>k</mi>
                          <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                          <mn>1</mn>
                        </mrow>
                      </msub>
                    </mrow>
                    <mo>)</mo>
                  </mrow>
                  <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <mn>2</mn>
                  </mrow>
                </msup>
              </mtd>
            </mtr>
            <mtr>
              <mtd></mtd>
              <mtd>
                <mi></mi>
                <mo>=3D</mo>
                <msub>
                  <mi>Q</mi>
                  <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <mi>k</mi>
                    <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                    <mn>1</mn>
                  </mrow>
                </msub>
                <mo>+</mo>
                <mrow>
                  <mo>(</mo>
                  <mrow>
                    <msub>
                      <mi>x</mi>
                      <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <mi>k</mi>
                      </mrow>
                    </msub>
                    <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                    <msub>
                      <mi>A</mi>
                      <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                        <mi>k</mi>
                        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                        <mn>1</mn>
                      </mrow>
                    </msub>
                  </mrow>
                  <mo>)</mo>
                </mrow>
                <mrow>
                  <mo>(</mo>
                  <mrow>
                    <msub>
                      <mi>x</mi>
                      <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
