<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"History">History</h2><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DStandard_deviation&amp=
;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D29" title=3D"Edit section: History"><span>edit=
</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The term <i>standard deviation</i> was first used in writing by <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Karl_Pearson" title=3D"Karl Pearson">Karl=
 Pearson</a> in 1894, following his use of it in lectures.<sup id=3D"cite_r=
ef-18" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standar=
d_deviation#cite_note-18"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>18<span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-19" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standard_deviation#cite_note=
-19"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>19<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]<=
/span></a></sup> This was as a replacement for earlier alternative names fo=
r the same idea: for example, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl=
_Friedrich_Gauss" title=3D"Carl Friedrich Gauss">Gauss</a> used <i>mean err=
or</i>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-20" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Standard_deviation#cite_note-20"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>20<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Standard_deviation_index">S=
tandard deviation index</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"m=
w-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.=
php?title=3DStandard_deviation&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D30" title=3D=
"Edit section: Standard deviation index"><span>edit</span></a><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The standard deviation index (SDI) is used in <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/External_quality_assessment" title=3D"External quality asses=
sment">external quality assessments</a>, particularly for <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_laboratory" title=3D"Medical laboratory">me=
dical laboratories</a>. It is calculated as:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Harr2012p23=
6_21-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standa=
rd_deviation#cite_note-Harr2012p236-21"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</spa=
n>21<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle {\text{SDI}}=3D{\frac {{\text{Laboratory mean}}-{\text{Consensu=
s group mean}}}{\text{Consensus group standard deviation}}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mtext>SDI</mtext>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mtext>Laboratory mean</mtext>
              </mrow>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mtext>Consensus group mean</mtext>
              </mrow>
            </mrow>
            <mtext>Consensus group standard deviation</mtext>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\text{SDI}}=
=3D{\frac {{\text{Laboratory mean}}-{\text{Consensus group mean}}}{\text{Co=
nsensus group standard deviation}}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/ee8e17cd8284aba39e50475e479d1127f76b031b" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.338ex; width:51.589ex; height:5.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {=
\text{SDI}}=3D{\frac {{\text{Laboratory mean}}-{\text{Consensus group mean}=
}}{\text{Consensus group standard deviation}}}.}"></span>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Alternatives">Alternatives<=
/h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[=
</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DStandard_dev=
