ves"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></=
span></div>
<p>Standard deviation is <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algebra" =
title=3D"Algebra">algebraically</a> simpler,<sup class=3D"noprint Inline-Te=
mplate" style=3D"margin-left:0.1em; white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:AUDIENCE" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Wikipedia:AUDIENCE"><span title=3D"An editor has requested that an exam=
ple be provided. (December 2024)">example needed</span></a></i>]</sup> thou=
gh in practice less <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robust_statist=
ics" title=3D"Robust statistics">robust</a>, than the <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Average_absolute_deviation" title=3D"Average absolute d=
eviation">average absolute deviation</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-22" class=3D"r=
eference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standard_deviation#cite_=
note-22"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>22<span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-23" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standard_deviation#cite_note-23"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>23<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
